    title: 'Web/Mobile Applications Developer (ASP.Net, MVC, HTML5, JS)',
    description:
      '\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href="http://www.responsegroupinc.com/Company/apply?jobTitle=Web%2FMobile+Applications+Developer+%28ASP.Net%2C+MVC%2C+HTML5%2C+JS%29"\u003eClick here to apply\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePosition Summary:\u003c/strong\u003e The position is responsible for designing and developing new applications, modifying, repairing or improving existing applications. The position is part of a development team that builds marketable applications to the emergency response industry primarily utilizing the Microsoft .Net development stack and hybrid mobile development frameworks.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eGeneral Duties \u0026amp; Responsibilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProvide support to other TRG Departments as directed.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eParticipate as a response member for immediate emergency response deployment as needed.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBe available for planned and unplanned exercises as directed.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eYou have a responsibility to respond/answer all TRG \u0026amp; Client communications.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDevelop proficiency in the IAP Software and a basic understanding of spill trajectory, modeling, and GIS mapping (Common Operating Picture).\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDevelops and ensures accurate and professional deliverables for clients.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAcquire a thorough knowledge of applications, systems, tools, and services provided by The Response Group.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBasic understanding of TRG products and services.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePosition Specific Duties \u0026amp; Responsibilities:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWork with the development team to create custom web and mobile application solutions from the ground up to support external client needs.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eParticipates in and leads discussions, as well as provides recommendations, on architecture and overall direction of company applications.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInvolved in all aspects of the product life cycle including solution design, implementation, and testing.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUse wireframes and mockups to build web pages, applications and software that lead to intuitive user experiences.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuilds web-based systems with the Microsoft .Net technology stack employing the best practices of SOA architecture using C#, ASP.Net MVC, with SQL backend databases.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuild hybrid mobile applications with HTML5 and JavaScript. Build native mobile applications with Xamarin.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with web development technologies HTML5, XML, CSS3, Ajax, JQuery, JavaScript, REST, and SOAP/XML Web Services.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with Microsoft SQL Server, T-SQL, stored procedures and triggers.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAdheres to change management process to resolve application defects and implement enhancements.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProvide technical documentation as needed.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMaintain client confidence and protect confidentiality of information.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCollaborate with other team members and stakeholders.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eServe at the direction of the Vice President of Software Development and perform additional duties as required.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWorking Conditions:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProlonged computer use in an office environment.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eRegularly required to lift up to 10 pounds, frequently lift up to 25 pounds, occasionally required lifting up to 50 pounds.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eVision requirements include close vision and ability to adjust focus.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eNoise level in the environment is moderate.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe position may require extended hours beyond the normal working hours to meet company objectives.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMinimum of 25% travel may be required throughout both domestic and international\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eQualifications:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e3+ years of experience in web/mobile application development utilizing .Net, C#, MVC, HTML/JavaScript, Web Services, Entity framework, SOA architecture required.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e3+ years of experience in SQL development with MS SQL Server required.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with Telerik tools and frameworks a plus.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with Xamarin mobile development a plus.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with ActiveDocs custom development a plus.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStrong working knowledge of Microsoft Visual Studio and Team Foundation Server (TFS)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFamiliarity with APIs, web services, and 3rd party platforms and libraries, such as Blog Platforms, Twilio, RSS, and Social Networks (e.g. Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, etc.) enabling social media integration and scalability.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience deploying highly available and scalable solutions using AWS (OpsWorks, ELB, S3, CloudFront, SQS) a plus.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExcellent oral and written communication skills required.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExcellent debugging and troubleshooting skills.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAbility to acquire a thorough knowledge of applications, systems and tools utilized at The Response Group.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAbility to work independently as well as in a small team environment and accomplish assigned tasks with minimal supervision.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAbility to adapt quickly to changes in application requirements.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEducation:\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBS or BA Degree in Business, Development or related field required.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e2-year College Degree or Training Certification preferred with 3-year experience in related field\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eTRG The Response Group LLC is an Equal Opportunity Employer.\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n',
