      '\u003cp\u003eIf you are a full stack WordPress developer that knows their stuff from the smallest lines of code up to the biggest plans for hosting and managing websites – and have deployed a network of WordPress sites across an organization – WE HAVE THE JOB FOR YOU!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe publish news and information on a daily basis across a network of sites, which presents us with challenges to keep moving forward quickly and to be successful in a ever changing media landscape. We are looking for someone who motivated, enjoys thinking outside the box, isn’t afraid of a challenge and is willing to take the initiative. We want you to help us be successful, which in turn will help you learn and grow.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWE NEED YOU TO...\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eKnow WordPress inside and out\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBe well versed in PHP/MySQL, jQuery and JavaScript overall\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHave experience building and deploying many WordPress sites across an organization\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBe familiar with, and be able to advise upon, the best plugins and services to integrate\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDesign a practical database schema for content, taxonomies and user roles\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWork directly with both our customer experience and advertising revenue teams to deploy features and technology to grow our business goals\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIntegrate third-party software and services into WordPress\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTest and QA development and work with others to help ensure quality work\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOffer best practices and knowledge on: Planning, Coding and Maintaining a network of sites with a good data structure\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBONUS POINTS IF YOU…\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLive in either North-Central Ohio or the Tri-Cities area in East Tennessee\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuild your own WordPress themes from scratch\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAre familiar with the publishing industry\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCan Deploy and Host sites on WP Engine\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHave Google DFP integration experience\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eKnow React.js\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAre familiar with APIs for, but not limited to, MailChimp, CXense, YouTube\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHave a proven track record showing how your planning and implementation of WordPress has delivered success\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWHO ARE WE?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe are a privately-owned newspaper group with news outlets and offices in several states. You will be working with a small, ambitious and fun team of designers and builders looking to push our sites forward using great tech, and smart decisions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eABOUT THE JOB\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou can work remotely as a contractor, or on-site as an FTE at one of our regional offices in Ohio or Tennessee. We have flexible hours and a casual approach that is balanced with meeting deadlines and being driven. If you work for us as a onsite full-time employee we allow flexible time for you to work at home as well as on-site.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePosition available to U.S. citizens only.\u003c/p\u003e\n',
