    title: 'Data Engineering Lead',
    description:
      '\u003cp\u003eTHE COMPANY\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eShare Local Media is a startup that works with well-known consumer brands (like Harry\'s, Casper, Blue Apron, and Uber) to plan and execute direct-mail campaigns. We offer a full-service solo-mail product where we manage the process end-to-end and we also offer a self-serve technology platform which allows brands to manage their own campaigns in a similar fashion to email or other online marketing channels. We are driven by our mission to offer superior service to our clients, leveraging both our industry expertise along with data and targeting to drive results.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTHE ROLE\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAs the Data Engineering lead, you would act as a hands-on technical lead and manager for a small team of data analysts. The Data Team works on client campaigns to perform analysis and reporting, unlocking insights and enabling data-driven decision making.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou would be reporting directly to the CTO and you will be working with stakeholders from across the organization to design and build a data pipeline which caters to our growing product and client needs. In this role, you would have significant ownership over the direction we take in building our data infrastructure and developing pipelines, tools, and methodologies to support data analysis.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis role includes engineering, statistics, project management, technical architecture, and people management. We are seeking an individual who can bring their technical skills and experience to the table and who can excel in the development and execution of our data strategy - this is a unique opportunity to make a lasting and immediate impact.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSKILLS \u0026amp; QUALIFICATIONS:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA degree in Computer Science, Statistics or a related field.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e5+ years of software engineering and/or management experience.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProven track record of building and shipping data-centric software products.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA passion for data and a strong understanding of statistics.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience working with large complex data sets.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAbility to collaborate with a diverse set of engineers, data scientists and product managers.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with data modeling, large-scale batch, and real-time data processing, ETL design, implementation and maintenance.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExcellent communication skills.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eComfort in a fast-paced startup environment.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eLOCATION \u0026amp; BENEFITS:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe role is based in our New York City headquarters. It is a Full Time role w. generous benefits and Flexible Vacation Policies.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eTO APPLY\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSend your resume and cover letter to \u003ca href="mailto:apply@sharelocalmedia.com"\u003eapply@sharelocalmedia.com\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n',
